\n<Manu><WordWrap>So this is the last area of the contest?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I did not expect it to be a mountain!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Shocking isn't it. But that's enough of that right now, your here to find Madam Oggay in order to win the contest.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Madam Oggay is located at the very top of the mountain. However very few made it to her because of challenging challenge
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Head towards the cave entrance in the middle to climb the mountain.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Do be weary of the things inside the cave's. I don't want you to get trapped or lost like the other contestants from the previous challenge.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I forgot to say this to you. But you'll have to face this challenge alone this time around.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Wait your leaving me right now? Out of all the times?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I'm not leaving you, just that I'll be here in the entrance to wait for your news. That's all Manu.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I am not allowed to be a guide this far in the contest. It's your journey and it should be you who would complete. Understand.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Once you completed Madam Oggay's challenge, meet me down here.

\n<CHEF><WordWrap>There you are Manu, so how was Madam Oggay?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Madam Oggay told me that you needed a chaperon in order to compete in the contest, let alone enter Gastropolis.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Just who are you, and what is going on then?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Tsk, she did not even try to wait a bit longer huh...
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I'll tell you everything you're at the Capitol...
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Just tell me what's going on exactly?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Well...I wouldn't want to spoil the surprise.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Head to the middle of the Capitol and there everything will be revealed.
